\intbl \ql \b Background\b0 \line PC Training and  Business College is registered with the Department of Higher Education and Training and is accredited to offer higher education programmes by the HEQC.\line \line In the AC meeting of 28 and 29 July 2010\'2C It was recommended that the decision be deferred for additional information\'3A\line 1. The programme design should be re-curriculated in conjunction with the higher certificate to ensure alignment and articulation.\line 2. The admissions requirements of the National Senior Certificate as indicated in the application are not suitable for entry into an advanced certificate. The institution must provide evidence that all references to this must be removed from marketing material. In addition\'2C for a programme of this level and nature\'2C computer literacy should be indicated as a prerequisite and not an element of the core programme design.\line 3. The assessment strategies lack detail and require clarity in terms of the number and types of tests\'2Fassignments\'2Fprojects\'2Fcase studies\'3B formative and integrated assessment exercises\'3B a record of students\'E2\'80\'99 performance\'2C problem areas identified and improvement plans\'3B examiners and moderators\'E2\'80\'99 reports and what measures have been taken to incorporate those into teaching and learning.\line 4. Although a list of prescribed books is provided for each module offered in this programme\'2C the institution should identify library resources specifically earmarked for this programme\'2C indicating how the theory \'2F taught aspects of the programme are linked to the independent resource aspects and how the institution\'E2\'80\'99s information resources support these aspects.\line 5. Applications for new programmes will only be considered for the following sites of delivery. Should the institution wish to offer on additional sites of delivery\'2C individual applications for each site of delivery will need to be made.\line 1. Smith Street\'2C Durban\line 2. Diagonal Street\'2C Johannesburg\line 3. Church Street\'2C Pretoria\line 4. Aliwal Street\'2C Bloemfontein\line 5. St George Mall\'2C Cape Town\line 6. Langalibalele Street\'2C Pietermaritzburg\line 7. Voortrekker Street\'2C Kempton Park\line 8. Main Street\'2C Johannesburg\line 9. Joe Slovo Street\'2C Durban.  \cell \pard 

